{"parse":{"title":"Condolence book","pageid":7076358,"revid":806356681,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Condolence_book_for_former_Prime_Minister,_Lady_Thatcher_(8640477662).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Condolence_book_for_former_Prime_Minister%2C_Lady_Thatcher_%288640477662%29.jpg/300px-Condolence_book_for_former_Prime_Minister%2C_Lady_Thatcher_%288640477662%29.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Condolence_book_for_former_Prime_Minister%2C_Lady_Thatcher_%288640477662%29.jpg/450px-Condolence_book_for_former_Prime_Minister%2C_Lady_Thatcher_%288640477662%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/45/Condolence_book_for_former_Prime_Minister%2C_Lady_Thatcher_%288640477662%29.jpg/600px-Condolence_book_for_former_Prime_Minister%2C_Lady_Thatcher_%288640477662%29.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"2136\" data-file-height=\"1424\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Condolence_book_for_former_Prime_Minister,_Lady_Thatcher_(8640477662).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A condolence book for <a href=\"/wiki/Margaret_Thatcher\" title=\"Margaret Thatcher\">Margaret Thatcher</a>, signed by visiting <a href=\"/wiki/G8_(forum)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"G8 (forum)\">G8</a> Foreign Ministers</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>condolence book</b> or <b>book of condolence</b> is a book in which people may record their <a href=\"/wiki/Condolence\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Condolence\">condolences</a> after a <a href=\"/wiki/Death\" title=\"Death\">death</a> or great <a href=\"/wiki/Tragedy_(event)\" title=\"Tragedy (event)\">tragedy</a>.\n</p><p>After the death of a leading figure or great disaster, condolence books are placed in public places for members of the general public to use.  When closed, the books are given to the relatives of the deceased or archived.  Reviewing a condolence book may help grieving relatives come to terms with the reality of their loss.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After especially notable deaths, official records of the condolences may be compiled and reprinted.  For example, after the assassination of <a href=\"/wiki/Abraham_Lincoln\" title=\"Abraham Lincoln\">Abraham Lincoln</a>, the Government Printing Office published a leather-bound, gilt-edged collection of official condolences in 1867.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Digital condolence books are now placed on the Internet so people may write their thoughts on-line.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Condolence_book&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Eulogy\" title=\"Eulogy\">Eulogy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Grief\" title=\"Grief\">Grief</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Memorial\" title=\"Memorial\">Memorial</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Tribute\" title=\"Tribute\">Tribute</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Condolence_book&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFJohn_Shep_Jeffreys\" class=\"citation\">John Shep Jeffreys, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=KJJeJv565ScC&amp;pg=PA236\"><i>Helping grieving people when tears are not enough: a handbook for care providers</i></a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Helping+grieving+people+when+tears+are+not+enough%3A+a+handbook+for+care+providers&amp;rft.au=John+Shep+Jeffreys&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DKJJeJv565ScC%26pg%3DPA236&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACondolence+book\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite id=\"CITEREFCarolyn_Lawton_Harrell\" class=\"citation\">Carolyn Lawton Harrell, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=uRdfSQHLaPoC&amp;pg=PA67\"><i>When the bells tolled for Lincoln: Southern reaction to the assassination</i></a></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=When+the+bells+tolled+for+Lincoln%3A+Southern+reaction+to+the+assassination&amp;rft.au=Carolyn+Lawton+Harrell&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DuRdfSQHLaPoC%26pg%3DPA67&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACondolence+book\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Books-aj.svg_aj_ashton_01.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4b/Books-aj.svg_aj_ashton_01.svg/34px-Books-aj.svg_aj_ashton_01.svg.png\" width=\"34\"